args:
At the port town, the publicity team decides to
promote the concert by putting on a show with
Siren's song and backup dancers—but the plan
backfires when the townsfolk react in horror.
While Siren claims not to be bothered,
she also begins to act a bit...strange.
Man, look at all the people. This is a\nperfect place to promote our show!
Now let us divide up into teams.\nWho wants to procure materials,\nand who will handle the publicity?
I already have this all worked out!
The best way to promote the concert\nis for me to SING!
All I need are two backup dancers.
Well, I ain't cut much rug recently,\nbut I guess I can—
My dancers will be Verica and Cleo.
As a fortune-teller, I'm not quite sure\nwhy I didn't see this coming.
Yeppers! The three of us dancing and\nsinging are gonna make ALL the feels!
Er, but surely you'd rather have Elisanne?
If we draft Elisanne into the publicity\nteam, the materials team is gonna be\ntotally disasterpants.
I mean, SOMEONE'S gotta yell at\nRanzal when he starts wandering\noff for food. It's inevitable!
But I don't know how to dance.
Look, this isn't a competition or whatever.\nYou don't need, like, REAL moves.\nJust sway to the beat and stuff!
It sounds like Siren has this all planned\nout, Cleo. Think you can make it work?
Well, if you are the one asking,\nI can't very well refuse.
Looks like we have our teams!
Let us all meet back at the beach\nonce our tasks are completed.
All right, my backup dancers!\nYou've got your swimsuits, right?
Are you truly all right with this, Verica?!
Cleoooo! Go get changed, girl!\nYou gotta get your dance on!
I am not wearing a swimsuit!\nI refuse! I refuse it utterly!
But you brought it and everything!
I totally don't know what that means,\nbut are you gonna help me or not?!
Look, this is gonna be super fun, so just\ngo put the stupid thing on already! Gosh!
I cannot. I'm afraid this sort of thing has\nhappened before, and I wasn't able to\ngo along with it then, either.
So you're saying you only agreed\nto dance, but not to wear the suit?
Correct—and I only agreed to that much\nbecause {player_name} asked.
Why do you have to be so stubborn\nabout such stupid stuff?!
Fiiiine! Whatevs. I guess I'll just take\nwhat I can get, even if it's super lame.\nNow let's get going already!
You guys are in for a SUPER treat,\nbecause the amazing Siren is\ntotally gonna perform for you!
Oh, good! It sounds like everyone\nis already quite familiar with her.
Then why do they look so...unhappy?
Cover your ears and run! Run awaaaaay!
HER SONG WILL DEVOUR YOUR MIND!
What?! Oh, that is simply absurd.
I saw it happen, man! There was this\ncrazy pirate monster at the beach\nand she totally bewitched it!
She's gonna turn our brains into mush!\nMush, I tells ya!
She musta got tired of sinking ships and\ndecided to wreak havoc on dry land!\nWe're doomed! Dooooomed!
Well, that certainly escalated quickly.\nEveryone scattered to the winds.
Heh. Cue the tumbleweeds, I guess.
Nope! No worries. We're aaaaall good.\nI literally thought that might happen,\nso I've totes got it covered.
Nope! Not a big deal at all.\nNooooo, buddy. Nooooope...
Hey, is it just me, or has Cleo seemed\nkinda...I dunno. Gloomy, I guess?
Yeah, but when we were all having fun\nback at the stage, she wouldn't join in.
And she never did put on her swimsuit.
Luca, please me tell me this conversation\nwas inspired by concern for Cleo and not\nsimply by your own lascivious curiosity.
What? No! This ain't about how hot\nCleo would look in a swimsuit!\nIt ain't about that AT ALL!
It's just that she's always cookin'\nand cleanin' and all that for us.
I mean, I know she's an attendant\nand that's kind of her job...
But it would still be nice to see her cut\nloose and have at least a little fun, yeah?
No, I understand. I was hoping she\nwould enjoy all of this, but...
Hee hee! Ohmigosh, guys, you got all\nKINDS of stuff! That's rad! Totes rad!
Uh, you got kind of a weird energy\ngoing on there, Siren. What's up?
Dude! What are you even TALKING about?!
I'm totally the same sweet, adorable,\nbeautiful Siren I always was! Tee hee!
Welcome back, guys. How'd it go?
Er, might I speak with you for a moment,\nPrince {player_name}?
...Wait, what?! But that's horrible!\nI'm going to march down there and—
Please do not. At this point,\nI think we need to watch and wait.
All will be well; Siren and Cleo both\npossess more than enough strength\nto overcome these challenges.
All they need is to find that last\nlittle spark of courage.
On some level, they already know that.
Did you see all that in your crystal ball?
I don't need a crystal ball to see it.
Everyone fears change. And while I know\nthey're both scared, neither of them are\nrunning away from it.
They're going to fight—against the\nobstacles before them, and against\ntheir own weaknesses.
Well, if you're so confident they'll be\nall right, I can back off for now.
As you say, we'll watch and wait.
But we should be ready to offer a helping\nhand if either of them asks for it.
Well, we've got lots of materials here,\nso I guess we'll head back to the Halidom.
